1,MCQ,Which default TCP port is typically used to discover DNP3 services?,502,20000,44818,102,20000,TCP 20000 is the assigned port for DNP3.
2,MCQ,What is the primary difference between Direct Operate and Select-Before-Operate?,DO requires TLS; SBO does not.,SBO is a two-step arm/fire sequence; DO is a single execution step.,DO is only for reading data; SBO writes data.,There is no difference.,SBO is a two-step arm/fire sequence; DO is a single execution step.,"SBO prevents accidental operation by requiring the point to be ""selected"" before it is ""operated""."
3,MCQ,Which DNP3 Function Code represents Direct Operate?,1,2,3,4,3,Function Code 3 is Direct Operate. FC 1 is Select.
